<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1580,1910]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
This species was described based on a pair of at least two females collected by Geraldo Cisneros on November 3 and 5 at Zamorano, 
<collectingCountry box="[579,697,1618,1644]" name="Honduras" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Honduras</collectingCountry>
. The female collected on November 3 was found at 
<collectionCode box="[1309,1399,1619,1645]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the number 
<quantity box="[432,538,1656,1683]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4957552" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="58888.0">58888 in</quantity>
the catalog of types. According to the original description and the label that the found specimen bears, it was designated by Cockerell as the 
<typeStatus box="[1005,1112,1694,1720]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen (
